{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/alternativa3d-more-3d-goodness-from-the-flash-player/","result":{"data":{"site":{"id":"Site","siteMetadata":{"title":"James Ford","author":"James Ford"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"c2764a84-f288-5ecf-8365-2e5b31aef4a7","html":"<p>3D Flash engines seem to be popping up everywhere at the moment.  [Although I wouldn't call that a bad thing] - Each one tends to take a different approach, do a different demo to distinguish themselves.  Take this for example, a very impressive looking offering from Alternativa3D;</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 500px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f1640e20cb5b54841ab71fb2af9c1dc8/41099/alternativa.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 55.99999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"alternativa\"\n        title=\"alternativa\"\n        src=\"/static/f1640e20cb5b54841ab71fb2af9c1dc8/41099/alternativa.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f1640e20cb5b54841ab71fb2af9c1dc8/f93b5/alternativa.jpg 300w,\n/static/f1640e20cb5b54841ab71fb2af9c1dc8/41099/alternativa.jpg 500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Papervision might have a lot of features and a large fan-base, but I have yet to see such a visually impressive demo [as this one].  And they've already sorted the first-person movement and collision detection.  It's also very cool that the demo seems to 'quickstart' - loading low-res textures to get you going as soon as possible, and streaming in higher res. ones while you play.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 500px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/fb3292c2211486679f8484f6d7b71f8d/41099/texturing.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 55.99999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"texturing\"\n        title=\"texturing\"\n        src=\"/static/fb3292c2211486679f8484f6d7b71f8d/41099/texturing.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/fb3292c2211486679f8484f6d7b71f8d/f93b5/texturing.jpg 300w,\n/static/fb3292c2211486679f8484f6d7b71f8d/41099/texturing.jpg 500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Progressive textures - how cool is that? (above)</p>\n<p>Of course, there's visual trickery going on here - the fantastic visuals are more down to excellent textures, rather than dynamic lighting or raytracing.  But that doesn't mean that the Alternativa3D team doesn't have that on their 'to-do' list...</p>\n<p>So, what are you waiting for?  Go check it out at <a href=\"http://blog.alternativaplatform.com/en/\" title=\"Open link in a new window\">alternativaplatform.com</a>.</p>","timeToRead":1,"frontmatter":{"title":"Alternativa3D - More 3D goodness from the Flash Player","date":"May 03, 2008","tags":["external-links","flash","papervision"],"url":null,"image":{"id":"22ce305e-bbe6-524f-8455-44fc1916fc98","childImageSharp":{"id":"ebc80ac9-0c03-5dbf-a160-50d6a7018c97","sizes":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7857142857142858,"src":"/static/f1640e20cb5b54841ab71fb2af9c1dc8/0f3a1/alternativa.jpg","srcSet":"/static/f1640e20cb5b54841ab71fb2af9c1dc8/426bb/alternativa.jpg 158w,\n/static/f1640e20cb5b54841ab71fb2af9c1dc8/6544a/alternativa.jpg 315w,\n/static/f1640e20cb5b54841ab71fb2af9c1dc8/0f3a1/alternativa.jpg 500w","sizes":"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px"}},"colors":{"vibrant":"#C5513A","darkVibrant":"#441C14","lightVibrant":"#E1A599","muted":"#848272","darkMuted":"#525046","lightMuted":"#C3C4BD"}},"description":null,"image_credit":null}}},"pageContext":{"prev":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/blog/open-screen-madness/","tags":["flash","flex","adobe","open-source"],"title":"Open Screen madness?","date":"2008-05-01T23:48:57.000Z","description":null,"image":{"childImageSharp":{"sizes":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7857142857142858,"src":"/static/1d7836713540bd4ae46c00a25543d411/0f3a1/open-screen.jpg","srcSet":"/static/1d7836713540bd4ae46c00a25543d411/426bb/open-screen.jpg 158w,\n/static/1d7836713540bd4ae46c00a25543d411/6544a/open-screen.jpg 315w,\n/static/1d7836713540bd4ae46c00a25543d411/0f3a1/open-screen.jpg 500w","sizes":"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px"}}}}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/blog/inline-javascript-and-the-defer-attribute/","tags":["javascript","embedding-flash"],"title":"Inline Javascript and the defer attribute","date":"2008-05-11T08:30:32.000Z","description":null,"image":null}}}}}